{"id": "UgwNbQbo7Mlz_f0tfmx4AaABAg", "videoId": "BqQNO7BzN08", "authorDisplayName": "@luxlamf", "publishedAt": "2023-04-14T17:10:24Z", "likeCount": 1, "textDisplay": "Remembering the 1st Evil Dead release and the effect it and Dead By Dawn (and then to a lesser extent  Army of Darkness ) had when released this trailer doesn't possess anything as unique and special  that those films have. This looks like yet another generic \" Blumehouse\" style horror movie that will be streaming by May and forgotten by Summer.  I'm willing to bet no one will be talking about it in 42 years like they still do the 1st Evil Dead. Just like the 1st TCM from '73, been a lot of horrible films after that no one remembers, they still talk about the 1st one though (That Biel from one was pretty good from 2003.) I hope it makes Bruce some money, but Evil Dead is about Ash. Read through the comments here, \"Groovy\" and other quotes from 35+ years ago  still thrown around because it's Ash not the monsters that make it an Evil Dead film. Maybe I will be surprised and find this one great, better yet maybe the Oldsmobile will make an appearance....", "parentId": null}
